All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Enum Summary 
    Class Description
    Board
    Creates a 6x6 board that contains four 3x3 squares.
    Client
    Class responsible for handling the connection between the client and the server.
    Coordinates
    Class responsible for creating a Coordinates object, used with all board manipulation moves.
    DummyBot
    Contains method used by DummyBot player, which implements the interface Player.
    Game
    Starts the actual game with two players.
    GameClient
    Interface containing all necessary methods that are to be used by the client.
    IntegrationTests  
    Move
    Class responsible for getting and setting parameters required to perform a move on the board.
    Player
    Contains stub methods used by all players of type Player: RealPlayer, DummyBot.
    RealPlayer
    Contains method to implement RealPlayer using interface Player.
    Rotation
    Enum responsible for the storage of two types of rotations: CLOCKWISE and COUNTERCLOCKWISE.
    Spot
    Enum responsible for providing the spots that are used on the board.
    Square
    Class responsible for creating the squares, four of which are required to create a board.
    Tournament
    Class for starting the system.
    TUI
    Class that prints the main menu and the help menu and the during the game.
    UnitTests  
    Utilities
    Class containing useful methods for translating the client syntax into game syntax.
